<BaseLayout title="About" description="Who is behind Stay Safe Guide, and the promise we make to readers.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About Stay Safe Guide</h1>

    <p>Hi, I'm Iulian. I started this site after I was scammed myself. It was a horrible
    few days, and the thing that stuck with me was how little plain, trustworthy help
    there was for someone in a panic who is not technical.</p>

    <p>So I went and learned how online security actually works. I hold CompTIA Security+
    and Microsoft's SC-900 certification, I'm studying toward Microsoft's SC-200, and I run
    a small home lab where I test the tools and settings I write about here. I'm honest about
    where I am: I'm earlier in my security career than the big review sites, and I think
    that is exactly why I can explain things the way I wish someone had explained them to me.</p>

    <h2>What this site promises you</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Plain English.</strong> No jargon, no showing off. If a term matters, I explain it once and move on.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest recommendations.</strong> I only point you to tools I would use or set up for my own family, and I tell you when a free option is good enough.</li>
      <li><strong>Clear about money.</strong> Some links earn me a small commission if you buy through them. That never changes which products I recommend, and it never costs you more. You can read the full <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Accuracy.</strong> I check my facts, date my guides, and update them when things change. Where something is my opinion, I say so.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who it's for</h2>
    <p>Anyone who wants to feel safer online without becoming an expert: parents, older
    relatives, small-business owners, and people who have just had a scare and want to
    fix it quickly.</p>

    <p>Got a question or spotted something I should correct? Please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
